Preconditions:
The input string "s" should not be null.
The input string "s" should not be empty.
The input string "s" should only contain characters 'B' and 'W' representing black and white balls respectively.

Postconditions:
The method should return a non-negative long value representing the minimum number of steps required to group all the black balls to the right and all the white balls to the left.
The order of the balls should not change, only their grouping should be modified.
The method should not modify the original input string "s".